This paper deals with the generation of pseudo code from source code, which is a software engineering task and falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). The approach involves the conversion of Python code into XML code, which is a programming language processing task and falls under the category of cs.PL (Programming Languages). The use of rule-based machine translation to generate pseudo code involves natural language processing, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The approach also involves the use of templates to generate pseudo code, which is a machine learning task and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the approach involves the use of important information extracted from the XML code, which is a task related to data mining and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
